(187, 'default', NULL, 1, 'published', '6-days-magical-kenya-safari', '/6-days-magical-kenya-safari', NULL, 'packages', '{\"title\":\"6 Days Magical Kenya Safari\",\"tour_highlights\":null,\"tour_duration\":6,\"tour_nights\":5,\"tour_primary_price\":null,\"tour_destinations\":[61,83,62],\"tour_experiences\":[\"a-hot-air-balloon-safari\",\"big-5-safari\",\"migration-safari\"],\"description\":\"A 6 days Magic Safari tour to Kenya\'s Amboseli National Park, Lake Nakuru National Park, and Masai Mara National Park is a once-in-a-lifetime experience.\",\"author\":\"0ddb50ce-bcbd-4bf3-b1e9-e573a9f89979\",\"tour_type\":null,\"tour_category\":[],\"featured_image\":\"kenya\\/masai-mara-two-elephants-shtstck.jpg\",\"template\":null,\"itinerary\":[{\"day_no\":1,\"day_title\":\"Arrive in Nairobi\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":2,\"day_title\":\"Amboseli National Park\",\"day_description\":\"A full day in this photogenic park. Morning and afternoon game drives. Meals and overnight at Amboseli Sopa or Kibo safari camp Amboseli National park is one of the most popular wildlife sanctuaries in Kenya. It is situated close to Kenya. It is situated close to Kenya and the Tanzania border, The Park lies at the foot of Mt. Kilimanjaro, the highest mountain in Africa (5,896m) whose snow-capped summit presents a splendid view on clear days. Amboseli National Park is often referred to as \\u201cThe home of Elephants\\u2019 some of the largest Elephant herds are found here.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":3,\"day_title\":\"Amboseli to Lake Nakuru National park\",\"day_description\":\"Depart Amboseli National Park for Lake Nakuru National Park. Hot lunch at Carnivore restaurant.  After lunch drive to Lake Nakuru National park. A brief stopover at the Great Rift Valley which is 8000 ft above sea level.  Continue with the journey to Lake Nakuru National park only to arrive in good time for evening game viewing in this park until 18:30 hrs when the park closes. Since your accommodation is right inside the park, you\'ll be able to see wildlife moving freely while you are at the lodge. The rest of the evening at the lodge inside the park.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":4,\"day_title\":\"Drive From Lake Nakuru to Masai Mara.\",\"day_description\":\"Early morning breakfast followed by another game in this park for four hours. Thereafter depart lake Nakuru National Park for Masai Mara \\u2013 the land of vast migrating animals. Arrival will be in time for late lunch at the selected accommodation. After lunch embarks on a game viewing in this park from 15:30 hrs until 18:30 hrs. The rest of the evening at the lodge located inside the park.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":5,\"day_title\":\"Full Day Game Drives Masai Mara\",\"day_description\":\"Full spent exploring Masai Mara in search of the Big 5. Morning and afternoon game drives are offered. Optional hot air balloon safari can be arranged at an extra cost of US$ 450 per person. Dinner and overnight stay at Ashnil Mara lodge\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":6,\"day_title\":\"Nairobi- Departure\",\"day_description\":\"After breakfast, we drive out across and over the rift escarpment to Nairobi. Transfer directly to JKIA for your outbound flight.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true}],\"includes\":[\"All activities (unless labeled as optional)\",\"All accommodation as stated in the itinerary\",\"A professional driver\\/guide\",\"Park fees\",\"All transportation (unless labeled as optional)\",\"All Taxes\\/VAT\",\"Roundtrip airport transfer\",\"All Meals (as specified in the day-by-day section)\",\"Drinking water on all days\"],\"excludes\":[\"International flights (from\\/to home)\",\"Additional accommodation before and at the end of the tour\",\"Tips\",\"Personal items\",\"Alcohol drinks\"],\"updated_by\":\"a0ef8da5-9dc9-4e55-9b48-0fe197a56747\"}', '2022-10-12 20:47:06', '2022-10-28 08:25:12'),
(188, 'default', NULL, 1, 'published', '7-days-river-crossing-tours-kenya', '/7-days-river-crossing-tours-kenya', NULL, 'packages', '{\"title\":\"7 Days River Crossing Tours Kenya\",\"tour_highlights\":null,\"tour_duration\":7,\"tour_nights\":6,\"tour_primary_price\":null,\"tour_destinations\":[84,62,83,60],\"tour_experiences\":[\"a-hot-air-balloon-safari\",\"big-5-safari\",\"game-drives\",\"migration-safari\"],\"description\":\"Prepare for a magical experience as you wind through Kenya\'s top national parks with splendid views and amazing wildlife.\",\"author\":\"a0ef8da5-9dc9-4e55-9b48-0fe197a56747\",\"tour_type\":null,\"tour_category\":[],\"featured_image\":\"kenya\\/wildebeest-crossing-mara-river-scaled.jpeg\",\"template\":null,\"itinerary\":[{\"day_no\":1,\"day_title\":\"Nairobi  to Aberdare National Park\",\"day_description\":\"Upon arrival at JKIA, you will be met by your driver\\/guide and transferred to the lush foothills of the Aberdares ranges. Arrive for lunch at the Aberdares Country Club, an elegant baronial style country home set in sprawling superbly landscaped gardens. Later, transfer to Aberdares National Park entering through the Ark gate. The first opportunity for wildlife viewing comes in a very unique setting, the Ark. The Ark was built to resemble the biblical Ark where you will stay overnight and have the opportunity to view animals as they come to drink along a natural waterhole. Here you may see elephant, rhino, bongo (rare nocturnal antelopes with black on tan stripes) and other species.\\n\\n**Dinner and overnight on full board.**\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":2,\"day_title\":\"Drive Aberdares to Samburu National Reserve\",\"day_description\":\"This morning, drive further north of Kenya to Samburu Game Reserve which is within the land of the colourful Samburu people, close relatives of the Maasai, and harbors a number of wildlife species found only north of the equator. It offers unique vistas of rounded and rugged hills and undulating plains. The mix of wood and grassland with riverine forest and swamp is home to a wide variety of animal and birdlife. Lunch is served at the Lodge and later in the afternoon proceed on a game viewing drive until sunset.\\n\\n**Dinner and overnight (full board).**\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":3,\"day_title\":\"Samburu - Lake Nakuru\",\"day_description\":\"After breakfast and check-out, drive down to Lake Nakuru, a protected game sanctuary for endangered species of the Black\\/ White rhino among other usual game such as the leopard and Lion. Late lunch at the camp followed by an afternoon game drive until sunset.\\n\\nDinner and overnight (full board).\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":4,\"day_title\":\"Drive Lake Nakuru - Masai Mara\",\"day_description\":\"Early morning game drive before returning for breakfast and departure to Maasai Mara Game Reserve, so named to mean the \\u201cspotted plains\\u201d in Maa language. This is home to the greatest concentration of large mammals and is widely recognized as Africa\\u2019s ultimate wildlife reserve. \\nThe park is famous for its annual migration of wildebeest. Transfer to the lodge with a game drive en route and after check-in enjoy hot lunch. Later in the evening enjoy a game viewing drive in this spectacular place of breathtaking sceneries, never-ending plains and the most abundant variety of wildlife remaining anywhere in the world. The landscape is made up of rolling savannahs dotted with patchy shrubs and bush thickets.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":5,\"day_title\":\"Full Day Game Drives Masai Mara\",\"day_description\":\"Full spent exploring Masai Mara in search of the Big 5. Morning and afternoon game drives are offered. During your stay, you have the opportunity to explore this great reserve in depth. \\n\\nThis day you may see elephant, giraffe, prides of lion, and thousands of impala, topi, grants and Thomson\'s gazelle. Birds are prolific including immigrants, 450 bird species have been recorded among them 57 birds of prey. \\n\\nThe Mara is the scene of annual migration of millions of wildebeest up from the Serengeti plains in search of water and grasses. You get a chance to visit a Maasai tribal village and enjoy entertainment by Maasai dancers. While in Mara, you will have the option to float above the Mara-Serengeti ecosystem on board a hot air balloon followed by a gourmet champagne breakfast (Options at an extra cost).\\n\\nAll meals and overnight\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":6,\"day_title\":\"Masai Mara - Nairobi\",\"day_description\":\"After breakfast, morning drive back to Nairobi with a game drive en route. Upon arrival check into your hotel for relaxation.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":7,\"day_title\":\"Departure\",\"day_description\":\"After breakfast, transfer to Jomo kenyatta International Airport for your flight home.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true}],\"includes\":[\"All transportation (unless labeled as optional)\",\"All activities (unless labeled as optional)\",\"All accommodation as stated in the itinerary\",\"A professional driver\\/guide\",\"Park fees\",\"All Taxes\\/VAT\",\"Roundtrip airport transfer\",\"All Meals (as specified in the day-by-day section)\",\"Drinking water on Safari\"],\"excludes\":[\"International flights (from\\/to home)\",\"Additional accommodation before and at the end of the tour\",\"Tips\",\"Personal items\",\"Alcohol drinks\"],\"updated_by\":\"a0ef8da5-9dc9-4e55-9b48-0fe197a56747\"}', '2022-10-12 20:50:01', '2022-10-28 08:54:02'),
(189, 'default', NULL, 1, 'published', '5-days-masai-mara-safari', '/5-days-masai-mara-safari', NULL, 'packages', '{\"title\":\"5 Days Masai Mara Safari\",\"tour_highlights\":null,\"tour_duration\":5,\"tour_nights\":4,\"tour_primary_price\":null,\"tour_destinations\":[62],\"tour_experiences\":[\"migration-safari\"],\"description\":null,\"author\":\"0ddb50ce-bcbd-4bf3-b1e9-e573a9f89979\",\"tour_type\":null,\"tour_category\":[],\"featured_image\":\"kenya\\/masai-mara-national-reserve-safaria.jpg\",\"template\":null,\"itinerary\":[{\"day_no\":1,\"day_title\":\"Arrive in Nairobi\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true,\"day_description\":\"We shall meet you upon arrival at the Jomo Kenyatta International airport (JKIA) followed by a free transfer to Hotel for an overnight stay in readiness for a memorable safari to Maasai mara game reserve.\"},{\"day_no\":2,\"day_title\":\"Drive to  Lake Nakuru National Reserve\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true,\"day_description\":\"After breakfast, you will be driven to Lake Nakuru and arrive around lunch time at Lake Nakuru Lodge.The Park also contains Kenya\\u2019s largest population of rhinos.   Lake Nakuru is one of the Rift Valley soda lakes at an elevation of 1754 m above sea level. It lies to the south of Nakuru, in the rift valley of Kenya and is protected by Lake Nakuru National Park.\"},{\"day_no\":3,\"day_title\":\"Drive Masai Mara Game Reserve\",\"day_description\":\"After breakfast, you will meet up with your guide and drive to Masai Mara and take your lunch boxes with.\\n\\nThe Maasai Mara National Reserve (MMNR) covers some 1,510 km2 (583 sq mi) in south-western Kenya. It is the northern-most section of the Mara-Serengeti ecosystem, which covers some 25,000 km2 (9,700 sq mi) in Tanzania and Kenya. It is bounded by the Serengeti Park to the south, the Siria escarpment to the west, and Maasai pastoral ranches to the north, east and west. Rainfall in the ecosystem increases markedly along a southeast\\u2013northwest gradient, varies in space and time, and is markedly bimodal. After game drive, head back to your lodge.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":4,\"day_title\":\"Masai Mara Game Reserve\",\"day_description\":\"Spend another day at the Mara in Masai Mara with morning and afternoon game drive. The Mara offers wildlife in such variety and abundance that it is difficult to believe: over 450 species of animals have been recorded here. \\n\\nYou will easily see lions, rhinos, hippos, crocodiles, giraffes, wildebeests, zebras, buffalo, warthogs, hyenas, jackals, wild dogs, buffalo, leopard, many kinds of antelopes, and elephant. It is in the Mara that perhaps the most spectacular event of the natural world takes place. This is the annual migration of millions of wildebeest and zebra from the Serengeti (Tanzania) in search of water and pasture. Following on their heels are the predators of the savanna- lion, cheetah, wild dog, jackal, hyena, and vultures\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":5,\"day_title\":\"Departure\",\"day_description\":\"Breakfast at the lodge. After breakfast, check out and drive back to Nairobi.\\n\\nAfternoon arrival at Jomo Kenyatta Airport for your departure flight.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true}],\"includes\":[\"Park fees\",\"All activities (unless labeled as optional)\",\"All accommodation as stated in the itinerary\",\"A professional driver\\/guide\",\"All transportation (unless labeled as optional)\",\"All Taxes\\/VAT\",\"Roundtrip airport transfer\",\"All Meals (as specified in the day-by-day section)\",\"Drinking water on all days\"],\"excludes\":[\"International flights (from\\/to home)\",\"Additional accommodation before and at the end of the tour\",\"Tips\",\"Personal items\",\"Alcohol drinks\"],\"updated_by\":\"a0ef8da5-9dc9-4e55-9b48-0fe197a56747\"}', '2022-10-12 20:51:29', '2022-10-28 08:00:02'),
(190, 'default', NULL, 1, 'published', 'gishwati-mukura-national-park', '/rwanda/gishwati-mukura-national-park', NULL, 'destinations', '{\"title\":\"Gishwati Mukura National Park\",\"description\":null,\"featured_image\":\"rwanda\\/lhoests_monkey-1920x1280.jpg\",\"parent\":null,\"seotamic_meta\":null,\"seotamic_title\":\"title\",\"seotamic_custom_title\":null,\"seotamic_title_prepend\":true,\"seotamic_title_append\":true,\"seotamic_meta_description\":\"empty\",\"seotamic_custom_meta_description\":null,\"seotamic_canonical\":null,\"seotamic_social\":null,\"seotamic_open_graph_title\":\"title\",\"seotamic_custom_open_graph_title\":null,\"seotamic_open_graph_description\":\"general\",\"seotamic_custom_open_graph_description\":null,\"seotamic_twitter_title\":\"title\",\"seotamic_custom_twitter_title\":null,\"seotamic_twitter_description\":\"general\",\"seotamic_custom_twitter_description\":null,\"seotamic_image\":null,\"updated_by\":\"0ddb50ce-bcbd-4bf3-b1e9-e573a9f89979\",\"blueprint\":\"park\"}', '2022-10-12 21:23:48', '2022-11-03 17:14:20'),
(191, 'default', NULL, 1, 'published', '4-days-rwanda-gorilla-trekking', '/4-days-rwanda-gorilla-trekking', NULL, 'packages', '{\"title\":\"4 Days Rwanda Gorilla Trekking\",\"tour_highlights\":null,\"tour_duration\":4,\"tour_nights\":3,\"tour_primary_price\":null,\"tour_destinations\":null,\"tour_experiences\":[],\"description\":\"Parc National de Volcans or Volcanoes National park was first gazetted in 1925. Decades later, this park assumed international recognitions when, in 1967, Diana Fossey an American naturalist arrive and set-up the Karisoke Research Centre. Diana\\u2019s research and exposure of the plight of the endangered gorillas decorates her legacy over three decades since her demise. Diana\\u2019s life is portrayed in the Movie, \\u201cGorillas in the Mist\\u201d!\",\"author\":\"a0ef8da5-9dc9-4e55-9b48-0fe197a56747\",\"tour_type\":null,\"tour_category\":[],\"featured_image\":\"rwanda\\/gorillas-(1).jpg\",\"template\":null,\"itinerary\":[{\"day_no\":1,\"day_title\":\"ARRIVE & TRANSFER TO KINIGI\",\"day_description\":\"Meet and assist upon arrival at Kanombe \\u2013 Kayibanda International airport in Kigali and transfer to Kinigi \\u2013 Ruhengeri near Parc National de Volcans. Transit time is approximately 3hrs. Spend the rest of the evening relaxing at Mountain Gorilla View Lodge.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":2,\"day_title\":\"GORILLA TRACKING & CULTURAL PERFORMANCE\",\"day_description\":\"Today is the long awaited day!! Early morning preparations for the activity, pack lunch, attend briefing by the Ranger-guide, get hold of a walking stick and follow the Ranger to the Sanctuary. It is imperative to respect and abide by the conservation rules therefore leave nothing but a footprint and take nothing but memories and photographs. Maximum time allowed with the fascination Gorillas is 1 hour. After gorilla tracking, return to Kinigi and attend a cultural dance performance. You may participate in the famous \\u201cIntore Dance\\u201d. Return to Mountain Gorilla View Lodge for the rest of the evening.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":3,\"day_title\":\"KIGALI \\u2013 CITY TOUR.\",\"day_description\":\"After an early breakfast, exit Kinigi or Parc National des Volcans area and transfer back to Kigali. Lunch break and embark on a Kigali City Tour! You will be privileged to witness the apex of human misery at the Gisozi Genocide Museum where the earth speaks of hatred and horrible brutality! The museum also serves a platform to learn more about other Genocides in the history of mankind. Proceed and visit local markets as well as worship places after which overnight at the Kigali Serena Hotel.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":4,\"day_title\":\"AIRPORT TRANSFER\",\"day_description\":\"Dawn breaks on Kigali town; enjoy last moments in the Land of 1000 hills, check-out and transfer to the airport.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true}],\"includes\":[\"All activities (unless labeled as optional)\",\"All accommodation as stated in the itinerary\",\"A professional driver\\/guide\",\"All transportation (unless labeled as optional)\",\"Roundtrip airport transfer\",\"Drinking water on all days\"],\"excludes\":[\"International flights (from\\/to home)\",\"Tips\",\"Personal items\",\"Alcohol drinks\",\"Services not mentioned in the program\"],\"updated_by\":\"a0ef8da5-9dc9-4e55-9b48-0fe197a56747\"}', '2022-10-12 21:36:56', '2022-10-30 09:45:06'),
(192, 'default', NULL, 1, 'published', '5-days-rwanda-gorilla-trekking-experience', '/5-days-rwanda-gorilla-trekking-experience', NULL, 'packages', '{\"title\":\"5 Days Rwanda Gorilla Experience\",\"tour_highlights\":null,\"tour_duration\":5,\"tour_nights\":4,\"tour_primary_price\":null,\"tour_destinations\":null,\"tour_experiences\":[],\"description\":\"Parc National de Volcans or Volcanoes National park was first gazetted in 1925. Decades later, this park assumed international recognitions when, in 1967, Diana Fossey an American naturalist arrive and set-up the Karisoke Research Centre. Diana\\u2019s research and exposure of the plight of the endangered gorillas decorates her legacy over three decades since her demise. Diana\\u2019s life is portrayed in the Movie, \\u201cGorillas in the Mist\\u201d!\",\"author\":\"a0ef8da5-9dc9-4e55-9b48-0fe197a56747\",\"tour_type\":null,\"tour_category\":[],\"featured_image\":\"rwanda\\/volcanoes-national-park-kinigi-headquarters.jpg\",\"template\":null,\"itinerary\":[{\"day_no\":1,\"day_title\":\"ARRIVE & TRANSFER TO KINIGI\",\"day_description\":\"Meet and assist upon arrival at Kanombe \\u2013 Kayibanda International airport in Kigali and transfer to City Blue Hotel in Kigali City. Superb comfort, dinner and overnight at City Blue.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":2,\"day_title\":\"KIGALI CITY TOUR \\u2013 TRANSFAR TO PARC NATIONAL DE VOLCANS\",\"day_description\":\"Dawn breaks on Hilly and Panoramic Kigali City, wake up, have breakfast and embark on a Kigali City Tour! You will be privileged to witness the apex of human misery at the Gisozi Genocide Museum where the earth speaks of hatred and horrible brutality! The museum also serves a platform to learn more about other Genocides in the history of mankind. Break for lunch and transfer to Kinigi \\u2013 Ruhengeri near Parc National de Volcans. Transit time is approximately 3hrs. Spend the rest of the evening relaxing at Le Bambou Lodge.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":3,\"day_title\":\"GORILLA TRACKING & CULTURAL PERFORMANCE\",\"day_description\":\"Today is the long awaited day!! Early morning preparations for the activity, pack lunch, attend briefing by the Ranger-guide, get hold of a walking stick and follow the Ranger to the Sanctuary. It is imperative to respect and abide by the conservation rules therefore leave nothing but a footprint and take nothing but memories and photographs. Maximum time allowed with the fascination Gorillas is 1 hour. After gorilla tracking, return to Kinigi and attend a cultural dance performance. You may participate in the famous \\u201cIntore Dance\\u201d. Return to Le Bambou Lodge for the rest of the evening.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":4,\"day_title\":\"GORILLA TRACKING & CULTURAL PERFORMANCE\",\"day_description\":\"Today offers a new dawn of a unique experience with Golden Monkeys! After an early breakfast, get hold of your packed lunch and undergo briefing. The Great Virunga Conservation in which Parc National des Volcans shares a significant portion, is where Golden Monkeys have a natural habitat. You will be privileged to have a rendezvous with the Old-World Golden Monkey. After this exhilarating experience with golden-apes, transfer to Kigali town and settle-in at City Blue Hotel.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":5,\"day_title\":\"FREE MORNING \\u2013 FLY OUT.\",\"day_description\":\"Morning at leisure in Kigali, you may sit-back and relax after breakfast or take a ride around to buy curio items\\/souvenirs. Depending on your flight arrangements, we shall conduct your airport drop-off and see you through to check-in for your final departure.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true}],\"includes\":[\"All activities (unless labeled as optional)\",\"All accommodation as stated in the itinerary\",\"A professional driver\\/guide\",\"All transportation (unless labeled as optional)\",\"Roundtrip airport transfer\",\"Drinking water on all days\"],\"excludes\":[\"International flights (from\\/to home)\",\"Tips\",\"Personal items\",\"Alcohol drinks\",\"Services not mentioned in the program\"],\"updated_by\":\"a0ef8da5-9dc9-4e55-9b48-0fe197a56747\"}', '2022-10-12 21:38:39', '2022-10-30 09:51:31'),
(193, 'default', NULL, 1, 'published', '6-days-rwanda-wildlife-safari', '/6-days-rwanda-wildlife-safari', NULL, 'packages', '{\"title\":\"6 Days Rwanda Wildlife Safari\",\"tour_highlights\":null,\"tour_duration\":6,\"tour_nights\":5,\"tour_primary_price\":null,\"tour_destinations\":null,\"tour_experiences\":[],\"description\":\"This 6 Days Rwanda Wildlife Safari will give you a chance to participate in two premium wildlife activities in Rwanda; Rwanda Gorilla trekking and Rwanda chimpanzee trekking. Both hikes can be challenging depending on where the chimpanzee or gorillas nested the previous night. The Chimp trekking differs from gorilla trekking because the sightings are a bit more sporadic and rushed, but worthwhile nonetheless as opposed to gorillas that stay for a while in one location.\",\"author\":\"a0ef8da5-9dc9-4e55-9b48-0fe197a56747\",\"tour_type\":null,\"tour_category\":[],\"featured_image\":\"rwanda\\/akagera-national-park.jpg\",\"template\":null,\"itinerary\":[{\"day_no\":1,\"day_title\":\"Arrival\",\"day_description\":\"Today you arrive for your 6 Days Rwanda Wildlife Safari. Our driver guide will be at the airport to pick you up and transfer you to your hotel after which you take on a Kigali city tour depending on your arrival time.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":2,\"day_title\":\"Transfer to Nyungwe forest national park\",\"day_description\":\"The journey from Kigali to Nyungwe forest national park will keep you a wake as you enjoy the various scenery. Nyungwe forest is located in southern Rwanda en route to Burundi and some parts of the Congo. The tour to Nyungwe forest will start early morning after your breakfast with our first short stopover in Nyanza before proceeding to Huye to tour the ethnographic museum. In Nyanza district there is an opportunity to visit the Kings palace museum which is an alternative to the ethnographic museum. You can discuss with your driver guide on which of the museums to stop at depending on your interests. They both share Rwanda\\u2019s cultural history but the ethnographic museum has more items and wide coverage. Arrive in Nyungwe forest later in that evening and proceed to our lodge for overnight.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":3,\"day_title\":\"Rwanda Chimpanzee trekking & Canopy walk\",\"day_description\":\"Chimpanzee trekking is an intimate experience with the forest and its inhabitants. Your driver guide will transfer you from your lodge to the briefing area in the forest where you are expected as early as 5.00 am. You will either be at the Uwinka trail head or the Cyamudongo trail head. The ranger guide will share chimpanzee trekking tips for you while in the forest.  The forest is rich with botanical diversity and home to 13 species of primates including Ruwenzori colobus, L\\u2019Hoest\\u2019s monkeys, Red-tailed monkeys, silver monkey, grey cheeked mangabey etc.,about 300 bird species with a number of Albertine rift endemics and several butterfly species.\\n\\nIn the afternoon \\u2013 take the canopy walk trail from the Uwinka trail head. Enjoy the views of the forest from this walk.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":4,\"day_title\":\"Transfer to Volcanoes national park\",\"day_description\":\"Today after breakfast, we start journey to the home of mountain gorillas in Rwanda \\u2013 Volcanoes national park in the Virunga region. Enjoy the winding roads and scenery of \\u201ca thousand hills\\u201d along the way and Lake Kivu. We arrive at your hotel later that evening \\u2013 rest enough ready for the gorilla experience tomorrow.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":5,\"day_title\":\"Gorilla trekking in Volcanoes national park\",\"day_description\":\"Gorilla trekking in volcanoes national park will most certainly be your highlight on this 6 days Rwanda primates safari. The experience coming face to face with the gentle giants in their natural habitats will remain with you forever. After an early morning breakfast, you will carry your day pack and the driver guide will transfer you to the briefing point. Your ranger guide in communication to earlier trackers will lead you to where the gorillas are. The trek can last from an hour to several hours depending on where the gorillas nested the previous night \\u2013 you need to be relatively fit to enjoy this experience.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":6,\"day_title\":\"Departure - End of 6 Days Rwanda Wildlife Safari\",\"day_description\":\"Wake up with memories of the previous day in the jungle with mountain gorillas. After a lazy morning, visit the gorilla guardians village, have lunch and later depart to Kigali for your return flight home to your hotel.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true}],\"includes\":[\"All activities (unless labeled as optional)\",\"All accommodation as stated in the itinerary\",\"A professional driver\\/guide\",\"All transportation (unless labeled as optional)\",\"Roundtrip airport transfer\",\"Drinking water on all days\"],\"excludes\":[\"International flights (from\\/to home)\",\"Tips\",\"Personal items\",\"Alcohol drinks\",\"Services not mentioned in the program\"],\"updated_by\":\"a0ef8da5-9dc9-4e55-9b48-0fe197a56747\"}', '2022-10-12 21:39:30', '2022-10-30 09:57:51'),
(194, 'default', NULL, 1, 'published', '4-day-magnificent-murchison-falls-safari', '/4-day-magnificent-murchison-falls-safari', NULL, 'packages', '{\"title\":\"4-Day Magnificent Murchison Falls Safari\",\"tour_highlights\":null,\"tour_duration\":4,\"tour_nights\":3,\"tour_primary_price\":null,\"tour_destinations\":null,\"tour_experiences\":[],\"description\":\"Murchison Falls \\u201cthe Summit of Adventure\\u201d.\\n\\nGazetted in 1952, Murchison Falls N.P. is Uganda\\u2019s oldest and largest National Park; it covers an area of 3,840sq kilometres. It is situated on the last stretch of Victoria Nile where it forms a delta to join L. Albert. This park is the only National Park in the world crossed by the Nile River, spectacular views of the Mighty Murchison Falls, over 451 recorded bird species and 76 mammal species including four of the Big Five.\\n\\nWildlife adventure at its best as you take a boat-ride on the Nile to the Bottom of Murchison Falls, Game-drive in the vast savannah grassland and Chimpanzee and other primates tracking in Kanio Pabidi Forest.\",\"author\":\"0ddb50ce-bcbd-4bf3-b1e9-e573a9f89979\",\"tour_type\":null,\"tour_category\":[],\"featured_image\":\"uganda\\/4-days-murchison-falls-safari.jpg\",\"template\":null,\"itinerary\":[{\"day_no\":1,\"day_title\":\"Arrival  Kampala\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":2,\"day_title\":\"KAMPALA \\u2013 RHINOS \\u2013 MURCHISON FALLS N.P\",\"day_description\":\"At 0630hrs, depart your hotel and route via the outskirts of the city heading to the Zziwa Rhino Sanctuary. This is a special occasion to track the extremely endangered White Rhino at ZZiwa. You will not only witness the most successful Rhino breeding project in the world but also contribute to their survival. Proceed to Masindi town and access the park via Kichumbanyobo gate. Take a scenic ride under shades of green, cross the season Sambiya River to the Nile River, continue and cross by ferry to the North Bank and settle-in at Paraa Lodge. Later in the evening, take a sunset game-drive and end your day in an adventurous style.  Accommodation at your preferred lodging facility.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":3,\"day_title\":\"SUNRISE GAME-DRIVE \\u2013 WATERFALL BOAT \\u2013 HIKE TO THE TOP OF MURCHISON FALLS.\",\"day_description\":\"Wake-up to the wild sounds and join your driver\\/guide on an early morning game-drives. Murchison Falls is haven to 76 mammal species and over 451 recorded bird-species. The north-bank section is savannah that is naturally decorated with borassus palms, acacia trees and riverine woodland. Looking out for Elephants, Lions, Leopards, Herds of Buffaloes, Rothschild giraffe, Hippos by the delta, Waterbuck, Bushback and Jackson\\u2019s Hartebeest among others. The birdlife is also rich with species like the Abyssinian Ground Horn Bill, Grey Herons, African Fish Eagle and Saddle-billed Storks among others. Return to the Lodge for lunch. At 1400hrs, transfer down to the pier\\/dock on the Nile River. Get on board and undergo briefing by the boat-guide. Against the current, start your boat-cruise heading to Murchison Falls. En-route, you are likely to see Hippos, Nile Crocodiles and other animal species grazing on the banks. Birding enthusiasts are likely to spot African Fish Eagles, Pied Kingfishers, Malachite Kingfishers, Red-throated bee-eaters and egret species among others. The boat shall pull over close to a rock before the \\u201cDevil\\u2019s Cauldron\\u201d, take pictures, sit on the rocks and exploit every moment with full sight of the Bottom of Murchison Falls. Dis embark from the boat and take a hike to the Top of Murchison Falls. At the top, you will bear witness to the great wonder of nature as Mighty Nile funnels itself through a 7 \\u2013 8 meter gorge. With incredible force, the Nile roars and groans creating a permanent spillage and a set of rainbow arches. Join your driver\\/guide and ride back to the hotel.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":4,\"day_title\":\"CHIMPANZEE TRACKING \\u2013 TO KAMPALA OR ENTEBBE.\",\"day_description\":\"As they call and hoot (chimpanzees) welcoming the light of the day, wake-up, take an early breakfast, check-out and transfer to Kanio Pabidi Forest.  Undergo briefing by the resident ranger\\/guide and follow him\\/her as he leads you to the chimpanzee sanctuary. Other resident primates are olive baboons, black and white colobus monkeys, red tailed monkeys and grey-cheeked mangbeys among others. Your informative guide shall show you the various types of trees and narrate stories about the forest in the ancient times of the traditional kings. The highlight of the tracking session is \\u201cman\\u2019s closest cousins\\u201d, the chimpanzees that you can see at close quarters. Return to the base and your waiting driver\\/guide shall route you back to either Kampala or Entebbe with lunch en-route.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true}],\"includes\":[],\"excludes\":[],\"updated_by\":\"a0ef8da5-9dc9-4e55-9b48-0fe197a56747\"}', '2022-10-13 15:02:37', '2022-10-30 10:02:18'),
(195, 'default', NULL, 1, 'published', '5-day-gorilla-trekking-safari', '/5-day-gorilla-trekking-safari', NULL, 'packages', '{\"title\":\"5-Day Gorilla Trekking Safari\",\"tour_highlights\":null,\"tour_duration\":5,\"tour_nights\":4,\"tour_primary_price\":null,\"tour_destinations\":null,\"tour_experiences\":[],\"description\":null,\"author\":\"a0ef8da5-9dc9-4e55-9b48-0fe197a56747\",\"tour_type\":null,\"tour_category\":[],\"featured_image\":\"uganda\\/5-day-gorilla-trekking-safari.jpg\",\"template\":null,\"itinerary\":[{\"day_no\":1,\"day_title\":\"KAMPALA \\u2013 BWINDI IMPENETRABLE FOREST NATIONAL PARK\",\"day_description\":\"At 0630hrs, pick up from your residence in Kampala or Entebbe and after a trip briefing, sign in our trip book and depart Kampala heading to Bwindi. We shall have an en-route stop at the Equator for a photo-opportunity and Mbarara town respectively for lunch. The last stretch of the Bwindi is a picturesque one that reveals the exhilarating nature beauty of the Kigezi Region. Check-in at your reserved accommodation facility for the rest of the night.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":2,\"day_title\":\"DAY TO TREK & TRACK GORILLAS\",\"day_description\":\"Wake-up to the hissing, whizzing and hooting sounds of the dense Bwindi Impenetrable Forest National Park. Pack lunch, water, emergency supplies and follow your-allocated ranger-guide to gorilla sanctuary. Trekking\\/tracking gorillas is a vigorous activity as tourists explore the abundant flora and fauna of the of Bwindi forest. Conformity to the park rules is vital and maximum silence is crucial for you to listen to rhythms of nature. As you approach gorillas maintain maximum calmness and exploit every moment of the strictly allocated one hour in the presence of the gentle great apes. With great memories of the wonders of nature, trek back to the staging area and join your driver back to your lodge.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":3,\"day_title\":\"BWINDI \\u2013 HEAD TO LAKE BUNYONYI\",\"day_description\":\"A misty, foggy and chilly morning ushers you to a new day in the dominion of the great apes, have breakfast, check-out and take meandering routes to Lake Bunyonyi. Cross by boat to Bunyonyi Eco Resort and settle in for the rest of the day.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":4,\"day_title\":\"DAY FOR EXCURSIONS AND LEISURE.\",\"day_description\":\"A fresh a gentle breeze conquers the early morning as the sun squeezes through the clouds to brighten the day. Have breakfast and embark on take a dug-out canoe ride on Lake Bunyonyi. Explore the artistic work of nature with a blend of terraced farm-land. Visit the Akampene Punishment Island and the Batwa Community. Return to Eco Lodge and relax for the rest of the day.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":5,\"day_title\":\"MAIN-LAND AND TRANSFER TO KAMPALA.\",\"day_description\":\"bre embark on a long scenic through villages, trading center and break for lunch either in Mbarara Town or at Igongo Cultural Center. Proceed to Kampala and drop-off at your residence or drop-off at Entebbe International airport to arrive on time for your onward flight out.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true}],\"includes\":[],\"excludes\":[],\"updated_by\":\"a0ef8da5-9dc9-4e55-9b48-0fe197a56747\"}', '2022-10-13 15:05:24', '2022-10-30 10:04:06'),
(196, 'default', NULL, 1, 'published', '6-day-kidepo-and-murchison-falls-wilderness-tour', '/6-day-kidepo-and-murchison-falls-wilderness-tour', NULL, 'packages', '{\"title\":\"6-Day Kidepo and Murchison Falls Wilderness Safari\",\"tour_highlights\":null,\"tour_duration\":6,\"tour_nights\":5,\"tour_primary_price\":null,\"tour_destinations\":null,\"tour_experiences\":[],\"description\":\"Explore two of Uganda\\u2019s national parks that are remarkable for wildlife viewing during this 6 days Kidepo valley and Murchison falls safari. Both game parks, Murchison Falls and Kidepo Valley, are located in the northern region of Uganda where the landscape is generally flat and is covered by vast savanna grasslands supporting plenty of animals and birds. Kidepo Valley National Park is Africa\\u2019s finest wilderness, rated the best on the continent for a spectacular landscape and great buffalo herds (CNN Travel 2013). It is tucked in the remote north eastern corner of Uganda, spanning the unadulterated ragged semi-arid valleys and savanna plains of the Karamoja province. The park supports plenty of wildlife including several animals and birds which are not found in other national parks in Uganda, such as Cheetahs and Ostriches. Due to its distant and remote location, the park is not easily accessible within a one day\\u2019s drive.\",\"author\":\"a0ef8da5-9dc9-4e55-9b48-0fe197a56747\",\"tour_type\":null,\"tour_category\":[],\"featured_image\":\"uganda\\/6-day-kidepo-and-murchison-falls-wilderness-tour.jpg\",\"template\":null,\"itinerary\":[{\"day_no\":1,\"day_title\":\"Transfer to Kidepo Valley NP\",\"day_description\":\"You will be picked up from your home in Kampala and transferred to the park at 6:45 am to avoid the morning Kampala traffic. Start the journey from Kampala through Uganda\\u2019s beautiful green undulating countryside. You will be driven to the north passing through towns like Luweero, Kigumba, Bweyale, Kamudini, and Gulu. You will have lunch in Gulu town, then drive on to Kitgum town, check-in at the lodge, where you will have dinner and rest as you prepare to transfer to Kidepo valley the following day.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":2,\"day_title\":\"A Drive to Kidepo Valley National Park\",\"day_description\":\"Early morning breakfast, check-out of the lodge, transfer from Kitgum town to the most silent and rarely visited park though highly bio-diversified Kidepo Valley national park. You will drive and go through the \\u201cKaramajongs\\u2019 \\u2018,one of the tribal communities and cattle-keeping people. then also check out their traditional way of life. You will then enter the park through the Katurum gate in midmorning and see a number of animals like; striped and spotted hyena, the greater and lesser Kudu, Jackson\\u2019s hartebeest, Oribis plus more others, check-in at the lodge, have lunch at lodge. Drive for an afternoon game drive before settling into the available lodge reserved for dinner and overnight stay.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":3,\"day_title\":\"Explore Kidepo Valleys Wildlife\",\"day_description\":\"At 6:30 am have a cup of coffee and head off for a morning game drive. A very good opportunity for you to catch lots of animals before they go to hide from the hot Ugandan sun as the day gets hotter game drive in the wild to see the early risers, you will drive to Kanangorok hot spring and the Narus Valley, these tracks support animals like elephants, Cape buffaloes, Rothchild\\u2019s, Giraffes, Burchell\\u2019s Zebras, Cheaters, Lions, Leopards, Guenther\\u2019s Dik diks, Common Elands, Bohor reedbuck and Birds species like the Giant Ostrich, Bustards, Secretary birds, Karamoja Apalis plus many more. Have a light breakfast, rest at the lodge, have lunch at Karenna and Kidepo to view and enjoy the cultural performances by the native Karamajong people. You will then return to the lodge for dinner and sleep.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":4,\"day_title\":\"Kidepo Valley and transfer to Murchison Falls National Park\",\"day_description\":\"Early morning breakfast, check-out of the lodge, transfer to Murchison falls national park via Gulu town where you will stop for your lunch meal. After transfer to the park, check-in at the lodge, rest at the lodge, have dinner and overnight stay.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":5,\"day_title\":\"Explore Murchison Falls National Park\",\"day_description\":\"At 6:30 am have a cup of coffee and head off for a morning game drive. A very good opportunity for you to catch lots of animals before they go to hide from the hot Ugandan sun as the day gets hotter. You will be taken to the Hippo pool where you can take some amazing photos. Head back to the Lodge in time for a heavy breakfast. \\n\\nAfter lunch, set out for a 2-hour boat cruise on River Nile, going upstream to the bottom of the Murchison Falls on river Nile. The boat ride offers a view of wildlife sightings \\u2013 crocodiles, hippos, and lizards are a common sight throughout the cruise. Big game such as buffaloes, elephants and antelopes, waterbucks, and giraffes can also be sighted drinking by the river banks and if lucky, you might even spot a leopard resting in the branches of one of the trees.   \\n\\nUpon reaching the bottom of the fall, leave the boat and set out for a 45-minute hike to the top of the falls where you will have a great view of the falls from above. Drive back to the Lodge and enjoy the rest of the evening.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":6,\"day_title\":\"transfer to Kampala and end of Uganda Tour\",\"day_description\":\"Have an early morning breakfast at 7:30 am, check out of the lodge, and transfer back to Kampala passing through masindi town with a stop at the Rhino sanctuary. Have Lunch at Javas Kisementi before being dropped at your hotel or airport.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true}],\"includes\":[\"Air-conditioned Vehicle + driver\",\"Park Entrance\",\"All meals\",\"One soft drink per meal.\",\"English Speaking tour guide\",\"Drinking water\",\"Boat cruise\",\"Rhino tracking\",\"Hiking on top of the falls\",\"Game drives\",\"Visit to  Kanangorok Host Springs\",\"Nature walks\",\"Scenic view of the Kidepo natural landscape\"],\"excludes\":[\"Visas\",\"Drinks\",\"Dining rooms\",\"Tips\",\"Porters\",\"Personal travel and baggage insurance\",\"Telephone bill\",\"Laundry and items of a personal nature\",\"Insurance\"],\"updated_by\":\"a0ef8da5-9dc9-4e55-9b48-0fe197a56747\"}', '2022-10-13 15:08:40', '2022-10-30 10:10:03'),
(197, 'default', NULL, 1, 'published', '6-day-ndutu-calving-season-serengeti-migration-safari', '/6-day-ndutu-calving-season-serengeti-migration-safari', NULL, 'packages', '{\"title\":\"6 Day Ndutu Calving Season Serengeti Migration Safari\",\"tour_highlights\":null,\"tour_duration\":6,\"tour_nights\":5,\"tour_primary_price\":null,\"tour_destinations\":[21,20,22],\"tour_experiences\":[\"a-hot-air-balloon-safari\",\"big-5-safari\",\"game-drives\"],\"description\":\"This itinerary is best experienced between the months of December and March when the Great Migration of wildebeest and zebra can be found on the southern plains of the Serengeti.\",\"author\":\"0ddb50ce-bcbd-4bf3-b1e9-e573a9f89979\",\"tour_type\":null,\"tour_category\":[],\"featured_image\":\"tanzania\\/wildebeests-migration-calving-safari-tanzania.jpg\",\"template\":null,\"itinerary\":[{\"day_no\":1,\"day_title\":\"Arrival\",\"day_description\":\"When you arrive at Kilimanjaro International Airport (JRO), Our guide will meet you directly and start your transit to Arusha\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":2,\"day_title\":\"Arusha - Tarangire National Park\",\"day_description\":\"Today we\\u2019ll be showcasing the often-overlooked Tarangire National Park, which we\\u2019ll reach by travelling west from Arusha for about two hours. The park is a nature lover\\u2019s dream, especially in the green season when its tremendous baobab trees are resplendent with emerald leaves. And if you\\u2019re visiting during the dry season, you can expect to see truly enormous herds of buffalo, wildebeest, and zebra\\u2014often numbering in the thousands. But no matter when you visit, Tarangire is perhaps best distinguished by its resident elephant population. These massive animals can always be relied upon to deliver a first-rate encounter in Tarangire. After finishing our all-day game drive and picnic lunch, we\\u2019ll settle in at the Tented Lodge just outside the park to spend our first night in the bush.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":3,\"day_title\":\"Tarangire - Serengeti ( Ndutu )\",\"day_description\":\"After enjoying our morning coffee or tea, we\\u2019ll head out for the far-reaching plains of the Serengeti. We\\u2019ll be travelling for approximately four hours today, but much of that time will be spent in the wildlife-rich environment of the Ngorongoro Conservation Area. When we reach Serengeti National Park, we\\u2019ll concentrate our game drives in the Ndutu region of the southern plains, famous for its year-round population of predators. The Ndutu area also happens to host the stunning wildebeest and zebra migration each year from December to March. This means that you\\u2019ll have the rare opportunity to see newborn wildebeest take their first steps, only minutes after they\\u2019re born. Later this evening, we\\u2019ll get settled in at the Ndutu Bush Camp, where we\\u2019ll spend the next two nights.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":4,\"day_title\":\"Serengeti Ndutu (Full Day)\",\"day_description\":\"The spectacle of the Great Migration is the star of the show in the Serengeti, and the wildebeest here synchronize their births during the months between December and March so that there are too many calves for predators to catch all at once. Thousands of the antelopes are born every day at this time of year, and this sudden influx of easy prey tends to attract the big cats of the Serengeti: lions, leopards, and cheetahs. We\\u2019ll spend the entire day in the park, stopping for a picnic lunch within sight of the herds. Tonight, we\\u2019ll return to the Ndutu Bush Camp, to enjoy dinner before comparing notes with other travellers around the campfire.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":5,\"day_title\":\"Serengeti - Ngorongoro crater\",\"day_description\":\"After treating ourselves to breakfast while watching the splendid Serengeti sunrise, we\\u2019ll enjoy one more game drive as we make our way out of the park en route to Ngorongoro Crater. This short trip takes only about two hours to cross the scenic Ngorongoro Conservation Area. The crater itself was formed millions of years ago by an erupting volcano\\u2014today, it\\u2019s a natural haven for all sorts of wildlife, including Africa\\u2019s Big Five. There\\u2019s no better reserve in Tanzania to find the lion, leopard, elephant, buffalo, and black rhinoceros all in one place. But there are also many other animals to see here, such as spotted hyenas, cheetahs, jackals, and more than 500 different kinds of birds. After leaving the crater tonight, we\\u2019ll check in at the Lodge nearby Karatu\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true}],\"includes\":[\"Transportation in a 4\\u00d74 safari vehicle\",\"Professional, English-speaking guide\",\"Overnight stays in safari tents or lodge\",\"Camping equipment (tents, sleeping mats, chairs, tables etc.)\",\"Meals according to the itinerary\",\"Mineral water\",\"All mentioned activities\",\"All national park fees\"],\"excludes\":[\"Flights\",\"Optional activities\",\"Alcoholic and soft drinks\",\"Visa fees\",\"Tips\",\"Personal spending money for souvenirs etc.\",\"Travel insurance\"],\"updated_by\":\"a0ef8da5-9dc9-4e55-9b48-0fe197a56747\"}', '2022-10-13 15:31:50', '2022-10-23 07:10:26');
