(207, 'default', NULL, 1, 'published', '3-day-trekking-mount-meru', '/3-day-trekking-mount-meru', NULL, 'packages', '{\"title\":\"3-Day Trekking Mount Meru\",\"tour_highlights\":null,\"tour_duration\":3,\"tour_nights\":2,\"tour_primary_price\":null,\"tour_destinations\":null,\"tour_experiences\":[],\"description\":\"3 Days Mt Meru trekking & tours via momella route is one of the best hiking in Tanzania as it includes wildlife spotting along Arusha national park. Mt Meru is the second highest Mt in Tanzania & the fifth in African landmass. Climbing Mount Meru in 3 days is a great hike & can be combined with Zanzibar beach holidays or short Tanzania safaris\",\"author\":\"a0ef8da5-9dc9-4e55-9b48-0fe197a56747\",\"tour_type\":null,\"tour_category\":[],\"featured_image\":\"mt-meru\\/4-day-mount-meru-trekking.jpg\",\"template\":null,\"itinerary\":[{\"day_no\":1,\"day_title\":\"Arusha \\u2013 Momella Gate 1500 m \\u2013 Miriakamba Hut 2500\",\"day_description\":\"The tour starts after breakfast in your lodge (1400 m) where you drive for about 30 minutes to Ngongongare gate via Usa river town. At the gate your guide will do all paper work before driving along Arusha National Park with some stops for wildlife spotting, reach Momella gate for final checkup of porters & luggage.\\n\\nYou may take long or short route but this will depend on the time of starting, during the hike way you will pass across Ngarenanyuki River and a beautiful waterfall at the base of Meru Mountain. You will possibly arrive at Miriakamba Hut (2500 m) before sunset, porters & your chef will have already be there  coffee or tea and a hot water for washing will be served. Enjoy the beautiful sunset & the area around.\\n\\nDinner and overnight at Miriakamba Hut (2,500 m).\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":2,\"day_title\":\"Miriakamba Hut 2,500 m \\u2013 Saddle Hut 3,500 m\",\"day_description\":\"After breakfast start your 3 days Mt Meru trekking along the steep path on the forest zone, see various birds and animal along the way. On the way you will view Mount Meru Crater & the Ash Tray. Reach Saddle Hut situated at the alpine desert zone for hot lunch (but this will depend on your pace).\\n\\nAfter Lunch and some rest, you have an option of acclimatization hike at Little Meru (3,820 m), this is a good hike with some great view of great Meru & the area around & it makes you ready for a night attempt on summit the main Meru Mountain. Early dinner will be served on this day so that you can have enough rest before your midnight summit attempt. Go to sleep as early as possible possibly around 19:00 hrs.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":3,\"day_title\":\"Saddle Hut 3500 m \\u2013 Meru Summit Socialist Peak 4,566 m \\u2013 Miriakamba 2,500 m\",\"day_description\":\"Wake up at 00:30 after midnight for tea and biscuit before you start your final push to the summit at 01:30 hrs. This final day of your 3 days Mt Meru trekking you will start by trading on the steep grade path up to Rhino point at (3800 m) then reach Cobra point at (4,350 m).\\n\\nFrom there the trekking will be on rocky ridge in between the Crater and the inner cliffs of Meru Mountain. Reach the summit during the first rays of sun from the East (4,566 m). During clear days, morning can be the best time to view his Majesty Kilimanjaro Mountain, the total cliffs of the crater drops intensely at almost 1000 feet or more.\\n\\nSpending sometimes at the summit for pictures before return back to Saddle Hut for some rest & afterward continue down to Miriakamba Hut & to Mommella gate for check out.\\n\\nThe van will have already be there waiting to take you back to Arusha or to the airport if flying with KLM at around 21.45 hours.\\n\\nIf you made it to the summit a certificate for Meru trekking (4,566 m) will be presented to you & for those who did the acclimatization hike at little Meru will also rewarded a certificate.\\n\\n**End of the Service.**\\n3 days Mt Meru trekking can be combine with our Tanzania wildlife safaris or Zanzibar beach holidays or both on request. Please let us know you wishes and desire.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true}],\"includes\":[\"Two way transfers to & from Arusha National Park\",\"2 Nights at Miriakamba & Suddle Huts\",\"Knowledgeable and experience Mt. Guide & Chef\",\"All meals while on the Mountain\",\"All permit & park fees\",\"TANAPA ranger fees\",\"Crew park fees & Salaries\",\"Rescue fee.\"],\"excludes\":[\"Arrival & departure transfers (upon request)\",\"Accommodation in Arusha. (Upon request)\",\"Tanzania Visa\",\"Tips for porters, cook & guide\",\"All items of person Nature.\"],\"updated_by\":\"a0ef8da5-9dc9-4e55-9b48-0fe197a56747\"}', '2022-10-14 00:12:31', '2022-10-30 10:26:15'),
(208, 'default', NULL, 1, 'published', '4-day-climb-mount-meru', '/4-day-climb-mount-meru', NULL, 'packages', '{\"title\":\"4-Day Climb Mount Meru\",\"tour_highlights\":null,\"tour_duration\":4,\"tour_nights\":3,\"tour_primary_price\":null,\"tour_destinations\":null,\"tour_experiences\":[],\"description\":\"4 Days Climbing Mt Meru the fifth highest Mountain in African landmass is via Momella route the only route on Meru. This Mountain is situated on Northern Tanzania and it is part of Arusha National Park. Climbing Mt Meru is an affordable tours & can be combined with our short Tanzania safaris.\",\"author\":\"a0ef8da5-9dc9-4e55-9b48-0fe197a56747\",\"tour_type\":null,\"tour_category\":[],\"featured_image\":\"mt-meru\\/little-meru-peak-1.jpg.1920x1440_q95_crop.jpg\",\"template\":null,\"itinerary\":[{\"day_no\":1,\"day_title\":\"Arusha \\u2013 Momella Gate 1500 m \\u2013 Miriakamba Hut (2,500 m)\",\"day_description\":\"After leisurely breakfast at your lodge\\/hotel in Arusha you will drive to Arusha National park first gate for registration then you will proceed to Momella Gate the starting point. When you and your guide are finishing other park formalities at Tanzania National Park (TANAPA) office, porters & cook will be organizing, packing & weighing all that needed for this hike. You will possibly have your packed lunch at the gate before starting\\n\\nAfterward you will start climbing Mt Meru, the first day is more or less similar to a walking safari, on the way  you should anticipate to spot some giraffes, zebras, antelopes and buffaloes. Since there is high possibility of spotting wildlife, you will be escorted by an armed ranger hired through TANAPA.\\n\\nOn the way you will pass the Ngarenanyuki River and if taking the short cut you will pass by a beautiful waterfall at the foot of Mt. Meru. Late afternoon you will arrive at Miriakamba Hut (2,500 m), your chef will prepare some coffee\\/tea and then hot water to wash, then will enjoy the beautiful sunset while waiting for dinner.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":2,\"day_title\":\"Miriakamba Hut 2,500 m \\u2013 Saddle Hut 3,500 m\",\"day_description\":\"After breakfast you will start your Mt Meru climbing on a steep path along the forest zone, various wildlife can be seen along the way. This trial offer views of Mt. Meru Crater as well as the Ash Tray. Arrive at Saddle Hut, the alpine desert zone during lunch time.\\n\\nAfter Lunch and some rest, if you wish you can climb Little Meru (3,820 m) with your guide for spectacular view of the area around Mount Meru and for further acclimatization. You will be served an early dinner so that you can have enough rest before your midnight summit attempt. Sleep around 19:00 hrs.\\n\\nOvernight at Saddle Hut at (3, 500 m)\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":3,\"day_title\":\"Saddle Hut (3,500 m) \\u2013 Meru Summit Socialist Peak (4,566 m) \\u2013 Miriakamba (2,500 m)\",\"day_description\":\"Wake up call will be at 00:30 hours tea and biscuit will be served before beginning your summit attempt at around 01:30 hrs. Climbing Mt Meru on this day start by trading on the steep grade trial up to Rhino point (3,800 m) then to Cobra point (4,350 m).\\n\\nFrom there you will walk on rocky ridge in between the Crater and the inner cliffs of Mt Meru. In early morning you will get to the summit (4,566 m) and witness the  sun rise from the East. Normally at this early Kilimanjaro is clearly seen, the complete cliffs of the Crater drops intensely at nearly 1000 feet or more.\\n\\nAfter spending sometimes at the summit return back to Saddle Hut for some leisurely brunch and afterward continue downward to Miriakamba Hut for dinner and overnight.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true},{\"day_no\":4,\"day_title\":\"Miriakamba \\u2013 Momella gate \\u2013 Arusha\",\"day_description\":\"Your Climbing to Mt Meru is now getting to the end, after some rest and leisurely breakfast, begin you way down to Momella gate, the hiking is through the forest where it is most likely to see some animals. If you took the long router on your first day then your descending will be via tululunsi water falls. At the gate you will meet your driver who is already there waiting for you. After say a farewell & tipping to you crew, you will drive back to Arusha.\\n\\nClimbing Mt Meru can be combine with our Tanzania wildlife safari or beach holiday in Zanzibar. Please let us know you wishes and desire.\",\"type\":\"day\",\"enabled\":true}],\"includes\":[\"Return Transfer Arusha National Park\",\"3 Nights overnight at the Mountain huts\",\"Trained and experienced Mountain guide & chef\",\"All meals while on the Mountain\",\"All park fees including VAT\",\"Ranger fees\",\"Crew Salaries and fees\",\"Rescue fee\"],\"excludes\":[\"Arrival & departure transfers (Unless Requested)\",\"Accommodation in Arusha. (Unless Requested)\",\"Tanzania Visa\",\"Tips\\/ Gratitude for crew\",\"All items of person Nature\"],\"updated_by\":\"a0ef8da5-9dc9-4e55-9b48-0fe197a56747\"}', '2022-10-14 00:13:08', '2022-10-30 10:30:43'),
